## Registered Native Tools in `@emmy/tools`

The package defines **9 native tools** in the frozen constant `NATIVE_TOOL_NAMES` (`packages/emmy-tools/src/native-tools.ts`):

| # | Tool | Description |
|---|------|-------------|
| 1 | **read** | Read a file; each line tagged with an 8-hex content hash for hash-anchored edits |
| 2 | **write** | Atomic file overwrite (open â†’ writeFile â†’ fsync â†’ close) |
| 3 | **edit** | Hash-anchored edit â€” references line hashes from the last `read`; stale hashes rejected |
| 4 | **bash** | Shell command execution (YOLO mode, with builtin + user-extensible denylist) |
| 5 | **grep** | ripgrep-style pattern search |
| 6 | **find** | Filesystem find (path, name, type filters) |
| 7 | **ls** | Directory listing |
| 8 | **web_fetch** | HTTP GET â†’ markdown (allowlist-gated per profile, plus recent-search-URL bypass) |
| 9 | **web_search** | Open web search via local SearxNG (conditional â€” only when profile enables it) |

## Runtime Discovery Flow

The discovery happens in **`packages/emmy-ux/src/session.ts`** inside `createEmmySession()`:

1. **`buildNativeToolDefs(nativeToolOpts)`** is called. Internally, this:
   - Calls `registerNativeTools()` with a **collector shim** (`{ registerTool: spec => collected.push(spec) }`) that captures every `PiToolSpec` emission
   - Maps each captured spec through **`toolSpecToDefinition()`** (in `tool-definition-adapter.ts`), which converts the Emmy-internal `{name, description, parameters, invoke}` shape into a pi 0.68-compatible `ToolDefinitionLike` with `{name, label, description, parameters, execute(...)}`
   - Returns `ToolDefinitionLike[]`

2. **`NATIVE_TOOL_NAMES`** is used as a **collision guard set** â€” when MCP tools are registered via `buildMcpToolDefs()`, any MCP tool whose name matches a native tool name is skipped (D-15 anti-shadowing rule)

3. The final **`customTools`** array is assembled as:
   ```
   [...nativeTools, ...mcpTools, ...memoryTools]
   ```
   (plus the `Agent` subagent tool if the profile has personas configured)

4. This array is passed to **`createAgentSessionFromServices({ customTools })`** â€” pi's session constructor â€” making it the authoritative tool registry

5. Separately, the tool descriptions are also **enumerated in the system prompt** (the `# Tools available` section in `toolDefsText`) so the LLM knows what tools exist at inference time

### Conditional Registration

- **`web_search`**: Only registered when `profile.harness.tools.web_search.enabled === true` AND env kill-switches (`EMMY_WEB_SEARCH=off`, `EMMY_TELEMETRY=off`) are not engaged
- **`memory`**: Only registered when the profile declares a `harness.context.memory` block and `resolvedMemoryConfig.enabled` is true
- **`Agent`** (subagent): Only registered when the profile has `subagents.enabled: true` with personas defined
